<doc id="803966" wikidata="Q2286966" url="?curid=803966" title="1905 Dutch general election">
<text>General elections were held in the Netherlands on 16 June 1905, with a second round in some constituencies on 28 June. The General League of Roman Catholic Electoral Associations emerged as the largest party, winning 25 of the 100 seats in the House of Representatives, with the Liberal Union coming second with 24 seats.

